FBIS4-11026 "drlat077_j_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 Panama Change 94's Carles Comments on Possible Front Against PRD Change 94's Carles Comments on Possible Front Against PRD PA2104014094 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in Spanish 1730 GMT 20 Apr 94 PA2104014094 Panama City Telemetro Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] [Text] Ruben Dario Carles, presidential candidate for the Civic Renewal Party, Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement [MOLIRENA], and the National Renewal Movement [MORENA], also commented on the possibility of forming alliances. [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Will there be sufficient political commitment to create the alliance MORENA and MOLIRENA have been calling for to establish a common front against the PRD [Democratic Revolutionary Party]? [Carles] Everybody agrees on that. [Reporter] Will Mr. Carles be willing to cede the head of the ticket to the Arnulfists, considering they are sticking to their stance? [Carles] I do not want to talk about what others think. I am saying the country knows our ticket is the best, from an individual and collective standpoint. We have programs that are not novels, works of fiction, songs, or poems, but facts -- the result of our experience, knowledge, and capability. We have the best team. You will not find any of them on any video. [end recording]
